NEW YORK Malcolm x, the
militant Negro leader who quit
the Black Muslims earlier this
q. year. was ordered by Judge
yesterday to vacate his six-room.
$4,000 home in the New York
City borough of Queens.


Civil Court Judge Maurice
VAIL ruled that Malcolm whose
real name is Malcolm x. Little

lost his right to the home when
he left the Muslims to form his
own cult. The Judge decided the
property clearly belong to the
Muslims' Temple of Islam, Inc. +,
which had bought it for Malcolm
as a residence or pars onage.
Malcolm's attorney said the de-
cision would be appealed.
